></a:tc><a:tc><a:txBody><a:bodyPr/><a:lstStyle/><a:p><a:pPr marL="0" algn="ctr" defTabSz="914400" rtl="0" eaLnBrk="1" fontAlgn="ctr" latinLnBrk="0" hangingPunct="1"><a:spcAft><a:spcPts val="600"/></a:spcAft><a:buNone/></a:pPr><a:r><a:rPr lang="en-US" sz="1400" b="1" i="0" u="none" strike="noStrike" kern="1200"><a:solidFill><a:schemeClr val="bg1"/></a:solidFill><a:effectLst/><a:latin typeface="+mn-lt"/><a:ea typeface="+mn-ea"/><a:cs typeface="+mn-cs"/></a:rPr><a:t>Dusty Tonkin</a:t></a:r></a:p><a:p><a:pPr algn="ctr" fontAlgn="ctr"><a:spcAft><a:spcPts val="600"/></a:spcAft><a:buNone/></a:pPr><a:r><a:rPr lang="en-US" sz="1050" b="0" i="1" u="none" strike="noStrike"><a:solidFill><a:schemeClr val="bg1"/></a:solidFill><a:effectLst/><a:latin typeface="+mn-lt"/></a:rPr><a:t>Chief Sales &amp; Marketing Officer</a:t></a:r></a:p></a:txBody><a:tcPr marL="6350" marR="6350" marT="6350" marB="0" anchor="ctr"><a:solidFill><a:schemeClr val="tx2"/></a:solidFill></a:tcPr></a:tc><a:extLst><a:ext uri="{0D108BD9-81ED-4DB2-BD59-A6C34878D82A}"><a16:rowId xmlns:a16="http://schemas.microsoft.com/office/drawing/2014/main" val="929626635"/></a:ext></a:extLst></a:tr><a:tr h="3393029"><a:tc><a:txBody><a:bodyPr/><a:lstStyle/><a:p><a:pPr marL="171450" indent="-91440" algn="l"><a:spcAft><a:spcPts val="600"/></a:spcAft><a:buFont typeface="Arial" panose="020B0604020202020204" pitchFamily="34" charset="0"/><a:buChar char="•"/></a:pPr><a:r><a:rPr lang="en-US" sz="1200" b="0"/><a:t>No centralized governance structure with clear decision rights</a:t></a:r></a:p><a:p><a:pPr marL="171450" indent="-91440" algn="l"><a:spcAft><a:spcPts val="600"/></a:spcAft><a:buFont typeface="Arial" panose="020B0604020202020204" pitchFamily="34" charset="0"/><a:buChar char="•"/></a:pPr><a:r><a:rPr lang="en-US" sz="1200" b="0"/><a:t>Limited finance oversight and few structured checks/balances</a:t></a:r></a:p><a:p><a:pPr marL="171450" indent="-91440" algn="l"><a:spcAft><a:spcPts val="600"/></a:spcAft><a:buFont typeface="Arial" panose="020B0604020202020204" pitchFamily="34" charset="0"/><a:buChar char="•"/></a:pPr><a:r><a:rPr lang="en-US" sz="1200" b="0"/><a:t>Limited exception reporting reduces transparency</a:t></a:r></a:p></a:txBody><a:tcPr marL="10625" marR="10625" marT="5312" marB="5312"><a:solidFill><a:schemeClr val="bg1"><a:lumMod val="95000"/></a:schemeClr></a:solidFill></a:tcPr></a:tc><a:tc><a:txBody><a:bodyPr/><a:lstStyle/><a:p><a:pPr marL="171450" indent="-91440" algn="l"><a:spcAft><a:spcPts val="600"/></a:spcAft><a:buFont typeface="Arial" panose="020B0604020202020204" pitchFamily="34" charset="0"/><a:buChar char="•"/></a:pPr><a:r><a:rPr lang="en-US" sz="1200"/><a:t>Current comp plans contain significant variation and complexity</a:t></a:r></a:p><a:p><a:pPr marL="171450" indent="-91440" algn="l"><a:spcAft><a:spcPts val="600"/></a:spcAft><a:buFont typeface="Arial" panose="020B0604020202020204" pitchFamily="34" charset="0"/><a:buChar char="•"/></a:pPr><a:r><a:rPr lang="en-US" sz="1200"/><a:t>Prospect and campaign data sit mainly within marketing systems</a:t></a:r></a:p><a:p><a:pPr marL="171450" indent="-91440" algn="l"><a:spcAft><a:spcPts val="600"/></a:spcAft><a:buFont typeface="Arial" panose="020B0604020202020204" pitchFamily="34" charset="0"/><a:buChar char="•"/></a:pPr><a:r><a:rPr lang="en-US" sz="1200"/><a:t>Lack of integrated data prevents analytics teams from identifying ideal customer profiles and decision drivers</a:t></a:r></a:p><a:p><a:pPr marL="171450" indent="-91440" algn="l"><a:spcAft><a:spcPts val="600"/></a:spcAft><a:buFont typeface="Arial" panose="020B0604020202020204" pitchFamily="34" charset="0"/><a:buChar char="•"/></a:pPr><a:r><a:rPr lang="en-US" sz="1200"/><a:t>Org cannot fully leverage AI and behavioral analytics without integrated data</a:t></a:r></a:p></a:txBody><a:tcPr marL="10625" marR="10625" marT="5312" marB="5312"><a:solidFill><a:schemeClr val="bg1"><a:lumMod val="95000"/></a:schemeClr></a:solidFill></a:tcPr></a:tc><a:tc><a:txBody><a:bodyPr/><a:lstStyle/><a:p><a:pPr marL="171450" indent="-91440" algn="l"><a:spcAft><a:spcPts val="600"/></a:spcAft><a:buFont typeface="Arial" panose="020B0604020202020204" pitchFamily="34" charset="0"/><a:buChar char="•"/></a:pPr><a:r><a:rPr lang="en-US" sz="1200"/><a:t>Leaders lack clear visibility into marketing pay and performance</a:t></a:r></a:p><a:p><a:pPr marL="171450" indent="-91440" algn="l"><a:spcAft><a:spcPts val="600"/></a:spcAft><a:buFont typeface="Arial" panose="020B0604020202020204" pitchFamily="34" charset="0"/><a:buChar char="•"/></a:pPr><a:r><a:rPr lang="en-US" sz="1200"/><a:t>Reporting does not provide clear insight into compensation outcomes</a:t></a:r></a:p><a:p><a:pPr marL="171450" indent="-91440" algn="l"><a:spcAft><a:spcPts val="600"/></a:spcAft><a:buFont typeface="Arial" panose="020B0604020202020204" pitchFamily="34" charset="0"/><a:buChar char="•"/></a:pPr><a:r><a:rPr lang="en-US" sz="1200"/><a:t>Compensation processes are decentralized, limiting consistency in reporting, forecasting, and plan management</a:t></a:r></a:p><a:p><a:pPr marL="171450" indent="-91440" algn="l"><a:spcAft><a:spcPts val="600"/></a:spcAft><a:buFont typeface="Arial" panose="020B0604020202020204" pitchFamily="34" charset="0"/><a:buChar char="•"/></a:pPr><a:r><a:rPr lang="en-US" sz="1200"/><a:t>Centralized governance would improve coordination across functions</a:t></a:r></a:p></a:txBody><a:tcPr marL="10625" marR="10625" marT="5312" marB="5312"><a:solidFill><a:schemeClr val="bg1"><a:lumMod val="95000"/></a:schemeClr></a:solidFill></a:tcPr></a:tc><a:tc><a:txBody><a:bodyPr/><a:lstStyle/><a:p><a:pPr marL="171450" indent="-91440" algn="l"><a:spcAft><a:spcPts val="600"/></a:spcAft><a:buFont typeface="Arial" panose="020B0604020202020204" pitchFamily="34" charset="0"/><a:buChar char="•"/></a:pPr><a:r><a:rPr lang="en-US" sz="1200"/><a:t>Managing multiple plans creates complexity and admin challenges</a:t></a:r></a:p><a:p><a:pPr marL="171450" marR="0" lvl="0" indent="-91440" algn="l" defTabSz=